<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-CA892D7D-7A16-494D-BA90-86FFFAFA0116" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-CA892D7D-7A16-494D-BA90-86FFFAFA0116" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">22 The function of the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Distribution PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA02 </compcodenr></comp></title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">How does the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Distribution PBA</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 22PBA02 </compcodenr></comp> function ? 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph ">Definition</ph></title><p class="- topic/p ">The <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Distribution PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA02 </compcodenr></comp> provides the following functions: 
</p><ul id="UL_D335F95806FE48C3B67069AE25BAA2ED" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_57B03E7873A34110B07A422E0D90114C" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Distribute 36V (unfused) to the <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Printhead Distribution PBA</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 22PBA03 </compcodenr></comp>,
</p></li><li id="LI_E05FEC2A86A64FCE87FFF80596A3CCCB" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Distributes 24V and 36V supplies towards multiple components (fused branches), 
</p></li><li id="LI_43E2582BAAF94B4FB2E05E97B9DC1BA5" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Some of these components contain a safety interlock circuit (relay). For each switched output an inrush prevention circuit is used. This circuit prevents high currents through the relay contact when it closes. 
</p></li><li id="LI_82871D95BB4E43689564359E1C859E0E" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> A “load on-demand” function. Switches on the bleeder resistors in case of a 36V reverse current to maintain a stable 36V voltage. 
</p></li><li id="LI_8EF0214B27EF43CFB1F95CBB132A0BC1" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Safety interlock circuit for a single mains branch (relay placed on PBA,AC_SWITCH). 
</p></li><li id="LI_55B76EB544A540A1B3022F0A3C9D5438" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Status signals. 
</p></li><li id="LI_F7A66F4EDC334F659C4DCF08106A0794" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Voltage detection circuitry for the supply voltages used for diagnostic purposes. 
</p></li><li id="LI_33A3BA7EE3EC4C038BA15939503734A1" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> LED’s to indicate power present or signal status. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="SECTION_CDD990D0C3454219815FF395CE0C5217" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Block diagram</title><fig id="GUID-AE23FE8A-958F-4284-A4B6-EE64550C52D5" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6855D77B-F6B9-47BF-B364-10523593F2A8-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6855D77B-F6B9-47BF-B364-10523593F2A8-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_1DB0748D4B4E4DEAAE0632FB719674AA" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Inputs</title><p class="- topic/p ">X1 
